'''Thyra Avis Mary Acres''' (née '''McNeill''', 26 March 1910 &ndash; 15 October 1994) was a New Zealand artist, writer, illustrator and conservationist. She was born in [[Wellington]], New Zealand, on 26 March 1910.<ref name="DNZB Acres"/>

Acres is best known for her comic strip about two [[pohutukawa]] fairies, ''Hutu and Kawa'', which was published weekly on the children's page of the ''[[New Zealand Herald]]'' from September 1950 to July 1960, and also was published as three books by [[Reed Publishing|A.H. & A.W. Reed]].<ref name="DNZB Acres">{{DNZB|title=Thyra Avis Mary Acres|first= Jill|last= Holt|id=5a3|accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref>

