{{Infobox power station | name = Jännersdorf Solar Park | name_official = | image = [[File:Solarpark Jännersdorf.jpg|frameless|Solarpark Jännersdorf]] | image_size = | image_caption = Jännersdorf Solar Park | image_alt = | location_map = Germany | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|53|21|N|12|03|E|region:DE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Germany | location = [[Prignitz]] | status = | construction_began = | commissioned = 30 June 2012 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | solar_type = pv | ps_units_operational = 167,550 | solar_site_area = {{convert|90|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}} | ps_electrical_capacity = 40.5 [[Megawatt|MW]]<sub>p</sub> | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_annual_generation = 38 [[GWh]] | website = | extra = }}
The '''Jännersdorf Solar Park''' is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Prignitz]], [[Germany]]. It has a capacity of 40.5 [[megawatts]] (MW) and an annual output of 38&nbsp;[[GWh]]. The solar park was developed and built by Parabel AG.
The project is built on a former military training area on {{convert|90|ha}}. The project is equipped with 167,550 [[photovoltaic modules]], with 25.6&nbsp;MW from [[Trina Solar]], 9.6&nbsp;MW from [[Suntech Power]] and 5.3&nbsp;MW from Hareon. The solar park was connected to the grid on 30 June 2012.<ref>[http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx Large-Scale Photovoltaic Power Plants] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101000000/http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx |date=January 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.parabel-solar.com/press-/786| title=Parabel AG puts 40.5 MW Jännersdorf Solar Park in operation| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140730151109/http://www.parabel-solar.com/press-/786| archive-date=2014-07-30}}</ref><ref>[http://www.pv-tech.org/news/brandenburgs_40.5mw_jaennersdorf_solar_park_officially_opens Brandenburg’s 40.5MW Jännersdorf solar park officially opens]</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.solarserver.com/solar-magazine/solar-news/current/2012/kw27/parabel-ag-completes-405-mw-jaennersdorf-solar-park-before-fit-cut-deadline.html| title=Parabel AG completes 40.5 MW Jännersdorf Solar Park before FIT cut deadline| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130222080842/http://www.solarserver.com/solar-magazine/solar-news/current/2012/kw27/parabel-ag-completes-405-mw-jaennersdorf-solar-park-before-fit-cut-deadline.html| archive-date=2013-02-22}}</ref>
